      "text": [
        " إِذَا عَطَسَ الرَّجُلُ فِي صَلَاتِهِ فَلْيَحْمَدِ اللَّهَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘When the man sneezes during his <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span>, so let him Praise Allah<sup>azwj</sup>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘In case of sneezing in Salah (prayer) one should say, ‘Tahmid, (all praise belongs to Allah).” "
        ]
      }
